        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 11:27PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1127 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Busby to 25 miles south of
Ashland, or extending from 26 miles southwest of Colstrip to 40
miles west of Broadus, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Ashland, Lame Deer, Busby, Birney, Birney Village,
Brandenberg, Muddy Cluster, Otter, Northern Cheyenne Indian
Reservation and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
